User Requirements and Application Specifications

1.Chosen Development Model
Development Model: Agile
Justification
Agile was chosen because our project is being developed step by step and the features may change during the process. 
In our case, the main part of the project is the labour operation tracking system, while the pregnancy tracking part supports it with patient history and monitoring data.
Since we are still improving features, interface design, and system structure, 
Agile is more suitable than Waterfall because it allows fast updates, team collaboration, testing after each part, and easier adaptation when new requirements appear.

2.User Requirements
a. Stakeholders 
1. Pregnant Woman / Mother:
Creates an account and logs into the system
Enters pregnancy details before labour
Tracks pregnancy week, symptoms, weight, and notes
Becomes the main patient whose data is used during labour monitoring

2.Woman's family:
Uses the women's user credentials to log in 
Gets track of woman's life situation during labour in real time such as: mother's / baby's heart rate; blood pressure; body temperature; situation (critical or not);
delivery (finished or not); cervical dilation 

3.Hospital admin:
Puts login information previously written by the hospital to be used continuously by the respective/responsible staff
Update labour status in real time


4.Developers:
Build the frontend,backend and database 
connects the pregnancy tracking part with the labour operation monitoring part
Maintains the system and improves missing features
3. Functional Requirements
a. Description
The system must specifically support pregnancy data management before delivery and labour operation monitoring during delivery.

Functional Requirements List
1.The system shall allow pregnant women to create an account.
2.The system shall allow registered users to log in using email and password.
3.The system shall display an error message when login credentials are invalid.
4.The system shall create a pregnancy profile for each registered mother.
5.The system shall allow the mother to enter personal pregnancy information.
6.The system shall store the due date of the pregnancy.
7.The system shall calculate the current pregnancy week automatically.
8.The system shall calculate the trimester automatically.
9.The system shall allow the mother to enter weekly weight records.
10.The system shall allow the mother to enter symptoms for each week.
11.The system shall allow the mother to enter pregnancy notes.
12.The system shall allow the user to edit pregnancy tracking entries.
13.The system shall allow the user to delete pregnancy tracking entries when necessary.
14.The system shall allow doctors to view the mother’s pregnancy history before labour.
15.The system shall create a labour monitoring record for a patient.
16.The system shall allow doctors to update the current labour or operation stage.
17.The system shall allow nurses to add labour progress notes.
18.The system shall record the condition of the mother during labour.
19.The system shall record the condition of the baby during labour.
20.The system shall attach a timestamp to each labour update.
21.The system shall display labour progress updates to family members.
22.The system shall allow admin to manage pregnancy and labour records.

